{
  "text": "Purification of Cdc48p MLY1600 cells (500 g) were suspended in 200 ml of buffer H (20 mM triethanolamine hydrochloride [pH 7.4], 1.5 mM EDTA, 1 mM MgCI2, and 5 mM I~-mercaptoethanol) containing 1 mM o-phenanthroline and 2 mM PMSF. An equal volume of glass beads (0.5 mm diameter) was added, and cells were disrupted by vigorous shaking seven times for 1 min each in a bead beater. The suspension was centrifuged at 3,000 x g for 10 min to remove cell debris and glass beads and subsequently at 18,000 x g for 30 min to sediment membranes and vesicular components. Proteins were precipitated with ammonium sulfate at 40% saturation, dissolved to an approximate protein concentration of 10 mg/ml, and dialyzed twice against 5 I of buffer H for 4 hr and 8 hr, respectively [CITATION_1] . The solution was applied to a 3 cm × 18 cm DEAE Sephacel (Pharmacia) column, washed with 1 vol of buffer H, and eluted with a 500 ml linear gradient of 0-600 mM NaCI in buffer H. Fractions of 7 ml were collected (Fr6hlich et al., Table 3 . Strains and Plasmids Used in This Study Strain1995). Fractions containing Cdc48p were pooled, adjusted to 50 mM potassium phosphate with a 1 M potassium phosphate (pH 7.4) stock solution, and applied to a 2 cm x 10 cm column of hydroxylapatite, which was prepared fresh each time using the method of [CITATION_2] . The colum n was washed with 2 vol of 40 m M potassium phosphate (pH 7.4), 1 mM MgCI2, 5 mM I~-mercaptoethanol and eluted with a 120 ml gradient of 50-200 mM potassium phosphate (pH 7.4) in 1 mM MgCI2, 5 mM J3-mercaptoethanol. Cdc48p-containing peak fractions that eiuted from hydroxylapatite and were free of major high molecular weight contaminants were pooled and concentrated by ammonium sulfate precipitation to 90% saturation. The precipitate was dissolved into 2 ml of buffer H100 (20 mM triethanolamine [pH 7.5], 100 mM NaCI, 1 mM MgCI2, 5 mM 13-mercaptoethanol) and loaded onto a 1 ml Mono Q column (Pharmacia). The column was washed with 2 ml of buffer H100, protein was eluted with a 20 ml of 100-600 mM NaCI linear gradient in buffer H (20 mM triethanolamine [pH 7.5], 1 mM MgCI2, 5 mM I~-mercaptoethanol), and 0.5 ml fractions were collected. Cdc48p-containing fractions were pooled and applied to a 125 ml Sephacryl $6 gel filtration column (Pharmacia) equilibrated in B88, 100 p.M ATP, 5 mM !5-mercaptoethanol. Fractions of 2 ml were collected, and those containing Cdc48p were pooled and concentrated at least 10-fold using Centricon 30 (Amicon) membranes.",
